The paper deals with physical layer security in cooperative networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of jammers to create intentional interference falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed schemes through simulations, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY).
